==English==
===Etymology===
Literally, to mix or join together. The word itself is a confusion of the prefix [[con-]] (a variant on the Latin prefix [[com-]], meaning [[with]] or [[together]]) and the verb [[fuse]] (meaning [[join]]).

===Transitive verb===
'''confuse''' ([[confuses]], [[confused]], [[confusing]])
#a. to thoroughly [[mix]], to [[confound]]; to [[disorder]]<br>b. ''obsolete''. to rout; [[discomfit]]
#a. to [[mix up]], to [[puzzle]], to [[bewilder]].<br>b. to make uneasy and ashamed; embarrass
#to [[mistake]] one thing for another

